  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This shipment was sent through Stop Hunger Now&apos;s partner, Heart to Heart International, to Nazarene Compassionate Ministries in Nepal. The Church of the Nazarene has more than 300 churches and church plants and 8,000 members in Nepal. Their focus following the earthquake will be to meet the needs of their neighbors, both through short-term emergency aid and longer-term community development efforts. 
To address the serious lack of food in affected areas, NCM leaders in Nepal would like to combine short-term food aid distribution with long-term seed and garden projects &#x2014; a successful strategy NCM has used in some rural areas of the country to create food security.</narrative>
  </description>
